"response_text": "The non-learning households (E-RO strategy) begin at 30 households and experience an initial sharp decline, dropping to ~20 households by time step 15. This decline accelerates further, reaching ~5 households by step 50, after which numbers stabilize around this level through the remaining steps. Key fluctuations include a brief spike to ~35 households at step 30, coinciding with reduced climatic variability in the preceding simulation runs. The final stabilized population reflects long-term equilibrium between household persistence thresholds and environmental carrying capacity under fixed genetic inclinations."  

}

